`[ExpectedException]` was removed in MSTest v4. Replace it with `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>` inside the test body.

**Before (v3):**
```csharp
[ExpectedException(typeof(InvalidOperationException))]
[TestMethod]
public void MyTest()
{
    service.DoWork();
}
```

**After (v4):**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void MyTest()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<InvalidOperationException>(() => service.DoWork());
}
```

**Key variations:**

| Scenario | Use |
|---|---|
| Async method | `await Assert.ThrowsExactlyAsync<T>(() => ...)` |
| `AllowDerivedTypes = true` | `Assert.Throws<T>` / `Assert.ThrowsAsync<T>` (matches derived types) |
| Setup before the throw | Keep setup outside the lambda; wrap only the throwing call |

The analyzer **MSTEST0006** could have flagged this while still on v3 â€” worth enabling if you have other projects to migrate.

